author: Zyklop Marco and Ngis
name: (Draft) Default Scan Methods
description: This default pack features standard scan routes based on the guide by Fiery and some other contributors.

path.description: If the teleport lands to the very north or in the south.western corner of the teleport area you the exact tile will not be in range.
If you land further to the south, run into range first.
Diving to the tile east of the spot should always be possible, no matter where the teleport landed.
Stepping in front of the cave entrance lines up a perfect {{dive}}-{{surge}} combination.
Stepping on any tile in a 3x3 area around the marked spot and then {{dive}}ing south-east lands you on the spot.
Click the target spot and surge anytime on the way there.
Click the target spot and surge after 1 or 2 ticks for the optimal path
Clicking the target spot will automatically take you to this tile. Run for 2 or 3 ticks and then surge and you will land on the target.
This isn't an easy spot to hit exactly. There are a lot of diagonal surges possible in this area as an alternative to improvise.
Any tile around the marked spot lines up the surge to land on the target spot.
